# Backend Patterns (NestJS + tRPC + REST)

Layer model, dependency rules, migration phases, and violation waivers: @architecture.mdc · full spec: `.index/architecture/TARGET_ARCHITECTURE.md`.

## Tech Stack
- NestJS 10 + TypeScript (strict)
- tRPC v11 for main API surface
- REST (`api-v1`) for auth/config endpoints and legacy upload compatibility
- MongoDB + Mongoose
- Zod shared contracts from `libs/shared-types`
- `zod` is also a direct dependency of `@meriter/api` (see `api/package.json`) for validation beyond shared-types
- tRPC uses the `superjson` transformer (`trpc/trpc.ts` `initTRPC`; dependency in `api/package.json`)

## Backend Structure

Full monorepo and layer overview: @architecture.mdc.

```text
api/apps/meriter/src/
├── domain/
│   ├── models/                # Mongoose schemas/documents (community, publication, vote, ...)
│   ├── services/              # Business logic + operational services/modules (publication, vote, wallet, permission, quota-reset, post-closing-cron, ...)
│   │   └── factors/           # Vote factor subsystem (role hierarchy, currency constraints, context mode, ...)
│   ├── aggregates/            # Domain entities/aggregates
│   ├── events/                # Domain events and event bus
│   ├── value-objects/         # Strongly-typed domain identifiers and VOs
│   └── common/
│       ├── helpers/           # Domain helpers (e.g. priority community logic)
│       └── constants/         # Domain constants (bootstrap, platform, roles)
├── trpc/
│   ├── routers/               # tRPC routers (publications, votes, wallets, ...)
│   ├── middleware/            # tRPC middleware (permission checks)
│   ├── context.ts             # Request context construction
│   ├── router.ts              # Main appRouter composition
│   ├── types.ts               # Type-only AppRouter re-export for frontend (see file header comment in code)
│   ├── trpc.service.ts        # DI-backed context/service wiring for tRPC
│   ├── trpc.module.ts         # tRPC Nest module
│   └── trpc.ts                # initTRPC + superjson + Sentry + HttpException mapping
├── api-v1/                    # REST modules (auth, config, legacy uploads) + api-v1/common/*
├── common/                    # Shared backend helpers/services/schemas/interceptors
├── decorators/                # Top-level Nest param decorators (e.g. `user.decorator.ts`; permission/Zod under `common/decorators/`)
├── updates-conductors/        # Update conductor subsystem
├── migrations/                # Migration scripts
├── seed-data/                 # Dev/demo seed snapshots, loaders, TSV/JSON helpers
├── i18n/                      # Backend locale message maps
├── config/                    # Runtime configuration + validation schema
├── telegram/                  # Telegram integrations (content pipeline helpers)
├── tg-bots/                   # Telegram bot module/services
├── domain.module.ts           # Shared domain wiring module
├── meriter.module.ts          # Root Nest module composition
├── meriter.controller.ts      # Root controller
├── meriter.service.ts         # Root app service
├── config.ts                  # Root-level app URL / bot env constants
├── main.ts                    # App bootstrap; mounts tRPC Express middleware at /trpc
├── permission.guard.ts        # REST permission guard
└── user.guard.ts              # Authenticated user guard
```

Note: additional migration/maintenance scripts also exist outside this tree under `api/scripts/*.ts`.

## Layer responsibilities (Clean Architecture)

| Layer | Live | Target | Agent rule |
|-------|------|--------|------------|
| Domain | `domain/services`, `domain/aggregates`, `domain/events` | + `domain/ports/` (Phase 3) | Business rules only; no tRPC/api-v1 imports |
| Application | scattered in routers (`createVoteLogic`) | `application/use-cases/` (Phase 2–3) | Orchestration; no `@InjectModel` / `@nestjs/mongoose` |
| Adapters | `trpc/`, `api-v1/` | `adapters/trpc|rest|mappers|presenters|resolvers/` (Phase 2) | Validate → use case → map → `ResourcePermissions` |
| Infrastructure | `domain/models`, `api-v1/auth`, `tg-bots`, `*-cron.service` in domain | `infrastructure/*` (Phase 2+) | Implements ports; cron invokes domain services only |

**Aspirational paths not on disk yet:** `application/`, `adapters/`, `domain/ports/`, `infrastructure/permissions/`. Phase 3 requires `PermissionGatesPort` + adapter before `CreateVoteUseCase` extraction.

## Module Wiring Rule
- Use a shared `domain.module.ts` for providers and model registration.
- Do not assume "one module per entity" layout.
- **New orchestration:** add `application/use-cases/[domain]/[action].use-case.ts` when layer exists; until then, do not deepen router god-methods — prefer domain service + thin router.
- **Legacy:** substantial logic remains in routers (`createVoteLogic`, merit history in `wallets.router`); extract per phase plan, do not add cross-router imports.

## API Layer Responsibilities

### tRPC (`trpc/routers` → target `adapters/trpc/routers`)
- Validate input with shared Zod schemas when possible.
- **Target:** thin controllers — delegate to application use cases; map via `EntityMappers`; attach permissions via engine + presenter.
- **Interim:** substantial logic in routers is legacy (V-03/V-04/V-08); do not import logic from other routers (e.g. `createVoteLogic` export pattern is waiver until Phase 3).
- No new REST business endpoints; dual transport = tRPC primary + REST auth narrow.
- tRPC procedures use shared middleware for Sentry profiling and `HttpException` -> `TRPCError` mapping (`trpc/trpc.ts`).
- Current router groups: `users`, `communities`, `auth`, `config`, `publications`, `comments`, `votes`, `polls`, `wallets`, `notifications`, `search`, `uploads`, `favorites`, `categories`, `about`, `tappalka`, `investments`, `teams`, `platformSettings`, `project`, `ticket`, `platformDev`, `meritTransfer`.
- Investments group is mounted as `investments` in appRouter, with implementation file `trpc/routers/investment.router.ts`.
- Platform dev group is mounted as `platformDev` in appRouter, with implementation file `trpc/routers/platform-dev.router.ts` (superadmin-only procedures).

### REST (`api-v1`)
- Used for selected flows (auth/providers, config, passkeys/WebAuthn, SMS/email OTP, phone call-check, magic-link), plus development/test auth endpoints (`fake`, `fake/superadmin`, `mock/:provider`), with shared REST helpers/services under `api-v1/common`.
- Upload REST endpoints are kept for backward compatibility and marked deprecated; prefer tRPC uploads endpoints for new code. Note: permission parity is not complete - `api-v1/uploads/community/:communityId/avatar` currently has a TODO for lead-role enforcement, while tRPC checks lead/superadmin.
- Reuse domain services and shared helpers where possible; current REST/tRPC layers also use dedicated enrichment/mapping helpers from `api-v1/common`.

## Bootstrap and Runtime Wiring
- `main.ts` mounts tRPC via Express middleware (`/trpc`) before Nest routes to correctly handle batched requests.
- Cookie parser is mounted on the raw Express app before tRPC middleware so authenticated and batched `/trpc` requests have parsed cookies in context.
- `main.ts` also calls `app.use(cookieParser())` again later (after tRPC setup); the file notes this mount is redundant but safe.
- Global exception/response handling is configured in bootstrap (`ApiExceptionFilter`, `ApiResponseInterceptor`).
- Sentry is initialized during bootstrap and also used in tRPC procedure middleware.

## Permission Flow

1. Route/middleware resolves actor and target context (`permission.middleware.ts`).
2. **`PermissionRuleEngine.canPerformAction`** — role × action from `permissionRules` (live).
3. **Post-type / product gates** — target: engine methods via **`PermissionGatesPort`** (Phase 3 stubs → Phase 5 inlined logic). **Interim:** gates live in `permissions-helper.service.ts` (V-06); engine must **not** import permissions-helper.
4. **`permissions.presenter`** (target Phase 5) — `ResourcePermissions` booleans + i18n disabled-reason keys only; no gate logic in presenter.
5. Domain services enforce wallet/quota/source rules (`CreateVoteUseCase` target).
6. Permission checks **before** side effects (inv-08).
7. Notifications via domain event → **`NotificationHandlersService`** (not inline `createNotification` in domain — V-05 waiver on `ob_vote_join_offer` until Phase 5).

**Nest DI (Phase 3):** `PermissionGatesPort` token → `PermissionGatesAdapter` in `infrastructure/permissions/permissions.module.ts`; adapter is sole infra importer of `permissions-helper`. Engine injects port via `@Inject(PermissionGatesPort)`.

**OD-3 sign-off:** product signatures on `.index/architecture/od3-matrix-signed.yaml` required before Phase 5 permissions migration merge.

Never rely on UI assumptions for security-critical checks.

### Auth Implementation Notes (Current Code)
- OAuth-related flows use the REST auth controller and Passport strategies (`api-v1/auth/strategies/google.strategy.ts`, `api-v1/auth/strategies/mailru.strategy.ts`); Yandex OAuth routes and callbacks are in `api-v1/auth/auth.controller.ts`.
- Passkeys support both split flows (`register/login`) and unified flow (`passkey/authenticate/start|finish`).
- Magic-link redeem endpoint includes in-memory IP rate limiting.
- Legacy `GET /api/v1/auth/me` exists and is marked deprecated in favor of `trpc.users.getMe`.

## Data and Schema Rules
- Shared API contracts: `libs/shared-types/src/` — canonical for cross-stack DTOs (inv-12).
- **`ResourcePermissionsSchema`** in `schemas.ts` is source of truth; Phase 1 deletes `api-v1/common/interfaces/resource-permissions.interface.ts`.
- Domain imports from shared-types: **allowlist only** (value-objects, taxonomy, value-rubricator, decree809-tag-remap) — not full `schemas.ts` (zone 6).
- Phase 1 stub: export `NotificationRoutingSchema` from `schemas.ts` (no backend runtime dependency yet).
- Backend-only schemas: `api/apps/meriter/src/common/schemas/` (e.g. `pagination.schema.ts` — canonical pagination; replace inline router pagination in Phase 1).
- Most Mongoose models are in `domain/models/**`; additional schemas can also exist in dedicated feature modules (e.g. `updates-conductors/model`).
- Auth persistence schemas are in `domain/models/auth/**` (`passkey-challenge.schema.ts`, `auth-magic-link.schema.ts`, `sms-otp.schema.ts`, `email-otp.schema.ts`).
- When changing contract shape, update both backend usage and frontend consumers.

## Service Pattern

```typescript
@Injectable()
export class ExampleService {
  constructor(
    @InjectModel(ExampleSchemaClass.name)
    private readonly exampleModel: Model<ExampleDocument>,
  ) {}

  async execute(input: Input): Promise<Output> {
    // business logic, validation, persistence
  }
}
```

## Router Pattern

```typescript
export const exampleRouter = router({
  create: protectedProcedure
    .input(CreateExampleSchema)
    .mutation(async ({ ctx, input }) => {
      return ctx.exampleService.execute(input);
    }),
});
```

## Stub procedures (resolved)

- `wallets.withdraw` / `wallets.transfer` — **permanent NOT_IMPLEMENTED**; rating withdrawal = `publications.withdraw`; peer transfer = `meritTransfer.*`; hide UI callers (Phase 1 grep).

## ESLint boundaries (Phase 0 — not landed)

Do not assume CI enforces layers yet. When Phase 0 merges, `import/no-restricted-paths` zones 1–7 apply (see @architecture.mdc). New code must not add domain→trpc or cross-router violations even before lint lands.

## Common Mistakes

❌ Putting business rules directly in tRPC routers/controllers (extract to use cases per phase plan)
❌ `PermissionRuleEngine` importing `permissions-helper` — use `PermissionGatesPort`
❌ Domain service importing `trpc/helpers` (V-01) or reading `process.env` for feature flags (V-07)
❌ Cross-router imports for vote economics (`publications` → `votes.createVoteLogic`)
❌ Inline notification creation in domain services (OD-12 / V-05)
❌ Duplicating validation instead of reusing shared schemas
❌ Skipping permission checks for "internal" endpoints
❌ Mixing REST/tRPC contracts without explicit mapping (inv-18: envelopes stay distinct)
❌ Applying tRPC permission middleware before `.input()` validation when resource IDs are extracted from input
❌ Treating deprecated REST upload endpoints as the primary API surface (OD-2 audit Phase 6b)
❌ Introducing backend-only DTOs into shared-types without cross-package need
❌ Assuming deprecated REST endpoints enforce the same permission checks as their tRPC replacements
❌ Adding `@nestjs/mongoose` imports in `application/**` (zone 5)
